thread.title: St. Paul Port Authority President Louis Jambois to retire
thread.title_full: St. Paul Port Authority President Louis Jambois to retire

author: Joe Kimball
title: St. Paul Port Authority President Louis Jambois to retire
text:
By Joe Kimball | 11:22 am 
Louis Jambois, who's been president of the St. Paul Port Authority for seven years, says he'll retire in February. He's 62. 
The Port redevelops property in St. Paul. Current big projects are the Macy's building in downtown and the former Midway Stadium site. It operates 21 business centers and four river terminals. 
Mayor Chris Coleman said in a statement: 
Louie has been integral to the revitalization and continued momentum and growth we are experiencing in St. Paul. We have a great deal to accomplish before he retires in February, and I am looking forward to that work together. 
The Port will start looking for a replacement this month.
